		<img width="2400" height="1153" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="person standing in front of rubble of destroyed mobile home park" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance.jpg 2400w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance-1200x577.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-disaster-insurance-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">Natural disasters—like Hurricane Andrew, which tore through Florida in 1992—are becoming increasingly common, and the US insurance industry is now facing an annual tab of $100-billion. Photo by Lannis Waters/Palm Beach Post/ZUMA Wire/Alamy Live News</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">In the Face of Mounting Climate Risks, the Insurance Safety Net Is Falling Apart</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">Natural disasters are costing the US insurance industry a fortune. What happens when no one wants to pick up the tab?</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by Lois Parshley 								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						November 27, 2023 | 3,000 words, about 15 minutes					</aside>
				</header>

